# Pull request template

When creating or updating a pull request (`gh pr create`, `gh pr edit`, or
`/commit-push-pr`), **read `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.MD` first** and
populate **all applicable sections** in the PR body. Do not substitute a
minimal custom summary.

## Required PR body structure

Use this structure (omit optional sections only when truly N/A; say so explicitly):

```markdown
**Jira ticket**

[Jira Ticket ID](https://phillipsauctions.atlassian.net/browse/TICKET-ID)

**Screenshots**
| Before | After |
| ------ | ----- |
| Paste Before Image | Paste After Image |

**Figma link**

[Figma Link](https://www.figma.com/file/FIGMA-LINK)

**Summary**

High-level overview and WHY the changes were made.

**Change List (describe the changes made to the files)**

- Additions, changes, and removals per file or area

**Acceptance Test (how to verify the PR)**

- Step-by-step verification instructions

**Regression Test**

- Steps to confirm existing behavior still works (or "N/A — …")

**Evidence of testing**

- Logs, screenshots, test command output, etc.
```

## PR creation checklist

- Branch name or commit context should supply the Jira ticket ID when available.
- PR title follows conventional commits (`feat(scope): …`, `fix(scope): …`).
- For UI changes, fill Screenshots and Figma link; use "N/A" with a short reason if none.
- Include reviewer checklist items from the template footer only when editing on GitHub;
  do not remove that block if the template is pasted into the PR description.
